        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://lore.kernel.org/lkml/20220920233947.0000345c@garyguo.net/\">Gary mentions</a> this pattern(<a href=\"https://godbolt.org/z/9n954cG4d\">playground example</a>):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[derive(Clone, Copy)]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span> <span class=\"nc\">Token</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">PhantomData</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;&amp;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span> <span class=\"nf\">with_token</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span>: <span class=\"nc\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">FnOnce</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Token</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;'</span><span class=\"na\">a</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">T</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt;\n    <span class=\"nc\">T</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Token</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">PhantomData</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>,used to represent a special context.<br>\nI couldn't find anything about it on google, does this have pattern have a name? Are there other examples/write-ups about how to use it?</p>",
        "id": 400215322,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1699051889
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>By context they mean a context like atomic. Inside atomic you cannot sleep. IIRC my OS course when the kernel traverses different contexts it means what the CPU would be allowed and what would be forbidden to do.</p>",
        "id": 400216390,
        "sender_full_name": "Martin Rodriguez Reboredo",
        "timestamp": 1699052577
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What I'm missing is how you prove you are in a specific context with the token.</p>",
