    {
        "content": "<p>I didn't get this part, why is it important that the token can be destroyed and how does it relate to mem::forget?</p>",
        "id": 400218385,
        "sender_full_name": "Ariel Miculas",
        "timestamp": 1699053898
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/291565-Help/topic/Rust.20.22Token.22.20pattern/near/400217654\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>a function from the standard library that also uses this pattern is <a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/thread/fn.scope.html\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/thread/fn.scope.html</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><code>scope</code> allows you to borrow non <code>'static</code> data. This means that at some point the data borrowed by the threads might no longer exist. For this reason the threads need to terminate before that happens. If we did not have the branded type API, but just a normal rust type, then the following would be possible:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">scope</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">thread</span>::<span class=\"n\">scope</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"kd\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">handle</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">scope</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">spawn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"o\">||</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"k\">loop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">         </span><span class=\"c1\">// do something with non `'static` data</span>\n<span class=\"w\">     </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">});</span>\n<span class=\"n\">forget</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">handle</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"n\">forget</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">scope</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Now nobody ensures that the thread actually terminates before the data is no longer alive.</p>",
        "id": 400218585,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1699054075
    }
]